    <text>
        <body>
            <head>200. Letter From President <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName>
                to Tunisian President <persName corresp="recQM7EFz4UiiW2Xj">Bourguiba</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d200fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                    National Security Affairs, Staff Material, Middle East, Subject File, Box 89,
                    Tunisia: 7/78–7/80. No classification marking.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1979-03-27"
                        >March 27, 1979</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mr. President:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>On the occasion of the fourth meeting of the U.S.-Tunisia <orgName
                    corresp="recHh5Ro1Ueoi84PG">Joint Commission</orgName>, I would like to extend
                my best wishes to you and to Prime Minister <persName corresp="rec8IOwPGGW4LB0wR"
                    >Nouira</persName>.<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d200fn2">An oral message
                    from <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName> to <persName
                        corresp="rec8IOwPGGW4LB0wR">Nouira</persName>, prepared by <persName
                        corresp="recSL4LMg1w3nFIv6">Quandt</persName> on March 27, is ibid.</note> I
                am very pleased that Secretary <persName corresp="recVgLVPXRruS2DSE"
                    >Kreps</persName> was able to participate in this meeting as the head of the
                delegation from the United States. Her presence is evidence of our continuing
                serious interest in <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>’s
                well being and security.</p>
            <p>I would like to take this opportunity to congratulate you on the very impressive <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="recmaQ3gdQeqBxn2G">economic development</rs> which
                    <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName> has achieved during
                the twenty-three years you have led your country. I am confident this <orgName
                    corresp="recHh5Ro1Ueoi84PG">Joint Commission</orgName> meeting will provide an
                occasion to strengthen and reinforce the <rs type="compound-subject"
                    corresp="reccrqkhzcDBZ13S2">friendship and cooperation</rs> which the United
                States and <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName> enjoy.</p>
            <p>Sincerely,</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Jimmy Carter</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
